programme.desc: After he becomes a viral online sensation, an up-and-coming stand-up comedian makes the big move to Los Angeles in the hopes of kickstarting a movie career. Meanwhile, his wife is in a long suffering live-in love, watching him follow his dream while she's stuck home, paying the bills and caring for their child.

programme.title: License to Drive
programme.desc: A teen flunks his driver's test but takes his grandfather's classic Cadillac out for a night on the town to impress a popular girl he likes. As the slapstick night progresses, he and his friends struggle to get themselves and the car home in one piece.

programme.title: Never Rarely Sometimes Always
programme.desc: A 17-year-old girl travels from a rural Pennsylvania town to New York City with her cousin to get an abortion (since a local abortion would require her parent's permission). Bureaucratic hurdles force both teenagers to remain in the city for far longer than they expected.

programme.title: Blade Runner 2049
programme.desc: In this stunning sci-fi sequel, a cop known as K hunts down android laborers who have gone rogue. But when he uncovers a conspiracy involving the robots, K searches for the one person who might have answers: a law-enforcement agent who once had his job.

programme.title: Safe House
programme.desc: In this pulse-pounding ride, a rookie CIA operative (Ryan Reynolds) goes on the run with a rogue former intelligence officer (Denzel Washington) after a South African safe house comes under attack by heavily armed mercenaries.

programme.title: Sermon on the Mount
programme.desc: Jerrod Carmichael carries intimate conversations with his family that explore common themes within the Black experience.

programme.title: True Grit
programme.desc: In the Coen brothers' stirring remake of the John Wayne classic, an alcoholic U.S. Marshal and an independent-minded 14-year-old girl track down her father's killer with the help of a Texas Ranger. As the three brave dangerous Indian territory, they discover their prey has fallen in with a more-experienced criminal.

programme.title: Man on a Ledge
programme.desc: An NYPD hostage negotiator attempts to talk cop-turned-fugitive Nick Cassidy (Sam Worthington) down from a high ledge, but she learns that he may have a hidden motive for threatening to take his own life in this pulse-pounding thriller.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city reels from Maladie's opera debut as Mundi takes a personal stake in tracking her down, and Amalia launches an investigation of her own. Meanwhile, the charitable Lavinia Bidlow seeks to destigmatize the Touched at a society event; Hugo Swann enlists Lavinia's younger brother Augie to help monetize his illicit enterprise; and a deranged doctor conducts a series of experiments.

programme.title: Dead Man Walking
programme.desc: Moving portrayal of real-life nun Helen Prejean, who develops a bond with a death-row inmate, in this powerful adaptation of Prejean's memoirs.

programme.title: The Last King of Scotland
programme.desc: This potent, powerful biopic is based on the reallife story about the brutal Ugandan dictator Idi Amin, his troubled reign and his mercurial relationship with a Scottish doctor.

programme.title: Ray
programme.desc: Add this Best Picture nominee about the life of singer Ray Charles (1930-2004) to the list of great screen bios. Best Actor Jamie Foxx is fantastic, bringing lots of heart and tons of soul to his portrayal of the music legend.

programme.title: Sling Blade
programme.desc: Released from an asylum after 25 years of incarceration for murdering his abusive mother, Karl Childers (Billy Bob Thornton) finds work as a repairman and befriends a trusting boy who has his own troubled family life. Thornton wrote and directed. Dwight Yoakam, J.T. Walsh, John Ritter.

programme.title: Life Is Beautiful
programme.desc: Roberto Benigni's Oscar winner for Best Foreign Language Film plays like two movies: a slapstick comedy and a heartfelt drama. Benigni plays an Italian Jew whose family is taken to a concentration camp, where he concocts a game to protect his young son.

programme.title: Rocky
programme.desc: A club fighter from Philadelphia who moonlights as a collector for a local mobster gets a shot at the big time when the heavyweight champion of the world gives him chance to fight for the belt on America's bicentennial.

programme.title: Argo
programme.desc: In this incredible thriller based on true events, a CIA agent uses the production of a fake science-fiction movie called \"Argo\" as a cover for a rescue operation in the Middle East during the Iranian hostage crisis.

programme.title: The Blind Side
programme.desc: This inspirational drama stars Sandra Bullock as Leigh Anne Touhy, a headstrong, wealthy Memphis woman who welcomes into her home Michael Oher, a deeply troubled African-American high-school student who turns out to be gifted at playing football.

programme.title: Dreamgirls
programme.desc: Supremely entertaining adaptation of the Broadway hit about the ups and downs of a 1960s girl group. Jennifer Hudson won a Best Supporting Actress Oscar for her role.

programme.title: Speed
programme.desc: A bomber has rigged a bus with a bomb and a cop must get on-board while it is traveling to figure out how to get the passengers off.

programme.title: The Hurricane
programme.desc: Denzel Washington in a striking performance as 1960s boxer Rubin \"Hurricane\" Carter, who went from contender to unjustly imprisoned convict-murderer to cause célèbre when people discovered that his conviction was the result of a case built on lies. Vicellous Reon Shannon offers moving support as a teen who believes in Carter and goes the distance to prove his innocence.

programme.title: The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
programme.desc: Tom Wilkinson headlines this uplifting comedy-drama about several British retirees who pool their resources to move to India, only to find that the hotel they're planning to reside at has fallen into disrepair. In time, they attempt to make the best out of a bad situation.

programme.title: The Ladykillers
programme.desc: In this screamingly funny update of the 1955 classic, a gang of thieves poses as a band to plot a riverboat heist, but their elderly landlady catches on. When she refuses to stay silent for a share of the take, they decide to silence her permanently. An arch remake of the 1955 British comedy classic.

programme.title: The Talented Mr. Ripley
programme.desc: Matt Damon, Jude Law and Gwyneth Paltrow star in this chilling adaptation of Patricia Highsmith's novel about a social-climbing psychopath. Damon is superb as Tom Ripley, a charming mimic whose obsession with a wealthy playboy (Law) turns deadly. Cate Blanchett, Philip Seymour Hoffman. Directed by Anthony Minghella.

programme.title: Jane Eyre
programme.desc: A young woman (Mia Wasikowska) must come to terms with her own turbulent past after fleeing from the estate where she worked as a governess for a wealthy man in this exquisite romantic drama based on the classic novel by Charlotte Brontë. Directed by Cary Fukunaga.

programme.title: Duplex
programme.desc: Eileen Essell is a scene-stealing delight as a crafty old lady whose new yuppie landlords (Ben Stiller, Drew Barrymore) want her out of her rent-controlled digs. Danny DeVito directed the killer black comedy from a script by Larry Doyle (\"The Simpsons\"). Harvey Fierstein, Wallace Shawn, Robert Wisdom, Justin Theroux, James Remar, Swoosie Kurtz.

programme.title: The Hoax
programme.desc: Richard Gere is a fascinating portrait in brazen panache as disgraced author and con artist Clifford Irving, who tricked the public in the early 1970s by claiming to have written an \"authorized\" biography of eccentric billionaire Howard Hughes. Marcia Gay Harden is excellent as Irving's misguided wife, and Alfred Molina gives a captivating performance as the author's right-hand man, who's fully aware that Irving has something up his sleeve. Directed by Lasse Hallstrom. Julie Delpy, Hope Davis.

programme.title: Benny & Joon
programme.desc: A repair-shop owner is in charge of taking care of his mentally ill sister. A losing bet forces him to also take in his friend's eccentric cousin, who immediately hits it off with his sister.

programme.title: Patch Adams
programme.desc: Robin Williams is charming as Patch Adams, a medical student in 1970s Virginia who uses humor to help heal his patients. While Adams' antics delight the people he's treating, they infuriate the rigid hospital establishment and threaten his career. The film is based on the true story of Dr. Hunter Adams. Monica Potter, Daniel London, Phillip Seymour Hoffman, Peter Coyote, Ellen Albertini Dow.

programme.title: Won't Back Down
programme.desc: In this riveting drama, two headstrong mothers wage a valiant struggle to save their children's troubled inner-city school, but find their forward-thinking efforts hampered at every turn by apathy and systematic bureaucracy.

programme.title: The Good Lie
programme.desc: Sudanese refugees get a second chance at life when a humanitarian effort brings them to America.

programme.title: Rounders
programme.desc: Matt Damon plays a law student whose poker skills create a dilemma of choice between pursuing the law and the excitement of testing himself against the best in the world of underground high-stakes games. The scales are tipped toward the latter when the young man must aid a jailbird pal (Edward Norton) in debt to mobsters. Gretchen Mol, John Turturro, Famke Janssen, John Malkovich, Martin Landau.

programme.title: Rambo (?)
programme.desc: Traumatized Vietnam veteran John Rambo (Sylvester Stallone) is back, and 15 years after his last mission he blows away baddies in a grind-house-style adventure that's brutal, bloody and never dull. Hauled from his Thai-jungle retirement to ferry missionary aid workers into Burma, the grizzled Rambo must return with a mercenary rescue team after the do-gooders are attacked by vicious Burmese soldiers. Julie Benz, Graham McTavish.

programme.title: The Devil Inside
programme.desc: In this chilling horror film, a woman (Fernanda Andrade) discovers that her mother was undergoing an exorcism when she committed three murders, and she travels to Italy with a documentary crew to uncover the full truth of what happened.

programme.title: Ouija: Origin of Evil
programme.desc: In this chilling horror sequel set in 1967 Los Angeles, a widow making ends meet as a psychic finds a Ouija board that enables her to talk to the dead. While it's great for business, the board also allows a ghost to possess her 9-year-old daughter.

programme.title: The Evil Dead (?)
programme.desc: Five vacationing college teens make an unplanned stopover in an abandoned mountain cabin surrounded by dense woods, where they discover an ancient-looking occult tome. Later, an ominous presence from the depths of the forest emerges, and things quickly become life-threatening for the coeds.

programme.title: Evil Dead 2: Dead by Dawn
programme.desc: Special effects and humor blend in a sequel about teens trapped in a haunted cabin.

programme.title: Army of Darkness
programme.desc: A discount-store employee is time-warped to a medieval castle, where he is the foretold savior who can dispel the evil there. Unfortunately, he screws up and releases an army of skeletons.

programme.title: The Invisible
programme.desc: This superb supernatural thriller keenly and frighteningly observes a golden-boy teenager (Justin Chatwin) as he hovers between the realms of the living and the dead after being viciously attacked and left to die. Marcia Gay Harden is outstanding as the young man's controlling and emotionally distant mother. Directed by David S. Goyer, the film is a remake of the Swedish thriller \"Den Osynlige,\" which was adapted from the novel by Mats Wahl. Margarita Levieva, Chris Marquette.

programme.title: Dead Heat
programme.desc: Two police officers lead an attempt to break up a crime ring that is made up of zombies in this comedic horror film, after one of the officers is bitten by an undead criminal.

In this flashy drama, New York's drug-and-sex-filled disco scene of the late '70s is seen through the eyes of a young man (Ryan Phillipe) whose life takes off when he obtains a job at an elite club owned by entrepreneur Steve Rubell (Mike Myers). Shane O' Shea (Phillipe) rises through the ranks from busboy to bartender and becomes a willing participant in the glitzy excess of the times. Neve Campbell, Salma Hayek, Mark Christopher, Sela Ward, Sherry Stringfield, Breckin Meyer.

programme.title: Conquest of the Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: In the fourth entry in the original series, Caesar, the son of Cornelius and Zira, leads a revolt against a fascist human society that has embraced ape slavery.

programme.title: Holy Rollers
programme.desc: In this tense crime drama based on a true story, a young Hasidic Jew (Jesse Eisenberg) is forced to go on the run when his family realizes the extent of his involvement in a New York City drug-trafficking ring. Directed by Kevin Asch.

programme.title: Motherless Brooklyn
programme.desc: A private detective living with Tourette's syndrome in 1950s New York City tries to solve the murder of his best friend and mentor. His case takes him through the Harlem jazz scene, the Brooklyn slums, and into the ranks of the city's most powerful men.

programme.title: Gangs of New York
programme.desc: In this sprawling epic about America, a young man in 1860s New York City seeks to avenge his father's death decades earlier at the hands of a hardened gang leader during a large skirmish between warring clans. He befriends the brutal crime lord, gaining his trust in order to get close enough to exact revenge.

programme.title: In Good Company
programme.desc: Paul Weitz (\"About a Boy\") directed this appealing and perceptive dramedy starring Dennis Quaid as a middle-aged ad exec who is demoted. Enter Topher Grace as his new boss, a 26-year-old hotshot who falls for Quaid's young daughter.

programme.title: Horrible Bosses
programme.desc: Hard-drinking friends Nick (Jason Bateman), Kurt (Jason Sudeikis) and Dale (Charlie Day) plot to kill their overbearing bosses with the help of a fast-talking ex-con in this blisteringly funny black comedy.

programme.title: This Means War
programme.desc: Big laughs abound when two top CIA spies find their enduring friendship put to the ultimate test when they engage in an all-out battle to win the affections of a beautiful woman after they discover they are both dating her.

programme.title: Last Christmas
programme.desc: A dysfunctional young woman working as Santa's elf at a year-round Christmas store in London finds her life taking an unexpectedly optimistic turn after becoming romantically entangled with a handsome and mysterious stranger over the holiday season.

programme.title: Ready or Not
programme.desc: Four college buddies find themselves on the adventure of their lives, when on the morning after a Las Vegas bachelor party, they end up stranded deep in Mexico penniless, being chased, falling in love, and fighting to make it back across the border in time for the wedding.

programme.title: The Good Lie
programme.desc: Sudanese refugees get a second chance at life when a humanitarian effort brings them to America.

programme.title: The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy
programme.desc: Thumbs up to this cosmic comic joyride adapted from the Douglas Adams sci-fi cult adventures. Mos Def is a blast as alien planet-trotter Ford Prefect, and Martin Freeman is equally fun as earthling Arthur Dent, his traveling companion and best friend. Sam Rockwell costars as Ford's cousin, Zaphod Beeblebrox, a galactic president with three arms and two heads. The animatronic monsters were designed by Jim Henson's Creature Shop. Zooey Deschanel, John Malkovich, Bill Nighy, Anna Chancellor.

programme.title: Reds
programme.desc: John Reed and Louise Bryant, two American journalists with a spotty romantic history, reunite professionally in this epic chronicle of the Bolshevik Revolution in Russia.

programme.title: View From the Top
programme.desc: Gwyneth Paltrow's high-flying turn propels this first-class comedy about flight attendants. Paltrow plays Donna Jensen, who leaves the trailer park to become a stewardess. With help from her mentor (Candice Bergen) and an oddball instructor (Mike Myers), she sets her sights on joining the prestigious Royalty Airlines. Christina Applegate, Kelly Preston.

programme.title: Tumbledown
programme.desc: In this witty, luminous and bittersweet comedy, the grieving widow of a singer-songwriter clashes with an acerbic journalist who arrives in her small Maine town announcing he's writing a biography about her late husband and his mysterious death. What begins as a clash of wills evolves into something more profound, as the journalist's presence helps her make peace with her husband's passing.

programme.title: Blackhat
programme.desc: A furloughed convict teams with a joint American-Chinese anticyber-theft task force to root out a hacker based in Southeast Asia.

programme.title: Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter
programme.desc: President Abraham Lincoln moonlights as a vampire hunter after learning that his mother was killed by bloodsuckers in this wildly fun supernatural action thriller adapted from the genre-bending novel.

programme.title: Darkness
programme.desc: This chilling blend of \"The Others\" and \"The Shining\" chronicles a family's nightmarish experiences in a haunted house in Spain.

programme.title: The Talented Mr. Ripley
programme.desc: Matt Damon, Jude Law and Gwyneth Paltrow star in this chilling adaptation of Patricia Highsmith's novel about a social-climbing psychopath. Damon is superb as Tom Ripley, a charming mimic whose obsession with a wealthy playboy (Law) turns deadly. Cate Blanchett, Philip Seymour Hoffman. Directed by Anthony Minghella.

programme.title: The Curious Case of Benjamin Button
programme.desc: In this remarkable tale, a man is born in New Orleans just after World War I, but he is already in his eighties and then proceeds to live his life aging in reverse into the 21st century, experiencing joy and sadness, loves lost and found, and the meaning of timelessness.

programme.title: The Adjustment Bureau
programme.desc: Rising politician David Norris (Matt Damon) battles a shadowy cabal known as the Adjustment Bureau, which has been altering time and space in order to keep him separated from a beautiful ballerina.

programme.title: XXX: State of the Union
programme.desc: Thrilling shoot-'em-up sequel about a special agent who's recruited to stop a plot to kill the president.

programme.title: Taxi Driver
programme.desc: A mentally unstable Vietnam veteran makes his living as a cabbie in New York, attempts to date a campaign worker, and befriends an underage hooker who he tries to get out of the life.

programme.title: Hoosiers
programme.desc: A disgraced basketball coach takes a job at a small Indiana high-school and leads the small squad on an improbable run for a state championship. Meanwhile, he helps the town drunk, a former basketball player, redeem himself.

programme.title: Mob Town
programme.desc: In 1957, an FBI agent teams up with a local police officer to monitor the activities of New York City's most notorious Mafia leaders as they prepare for a large-scale gathering in upstate New York. It is up to the unlikely duo to piece together the purpose of such a meeting and thwart any instances of violence that may erupt as a result.

programme.title: Red
programme.desc: Retired CIA hit man Frank Moses (Bruce Willis) and his former colleagues race to find out why they've been targeted for death by their former organization and uncover a conspiracy implicating some prominent politicians in this rousing action comedy.

programme.title: The Godfather
programme.desc: Best Picture chronicles the epic tale of a 1940's mobster family in New York City, where the father builds an organized-crime empire and his three sons, to varying degrees, follow in his footsteps. Marlon Brando won Best Actor as the head of the \"family.\".

programme.title: The Godfather, Part II
programme.desc: This sequel follows Vito Corleone's rise to the top of his Mafia family and his son Michael's fall from grace after taking over for his father. Best Picture winner.

programme.title: Mario Puzo's The Godfather, Coda: The Death of Michael Corleone (?)
programme.desc: Michael Corleone, now in his 60s, seeks to free his family from crime and find a suitable successor to his empire. That successor could be fiery Vincent, but he may also be the spark that turns Michael's hope of business legitimacy into an inferno{ of mob violence. Francis Ford Coppola brings a definitive new edit and restoration of the final film in his epic Godfather trilogy.

programme.title: True History of the Kelly Gang
programme.desc: Set in late 1800s Australia, True History of the Kelly Gang tells the story of Ned Kelly, the leader of one of the most prolific gangs Australia has ever seen. As a young child, Ned is exposed to poverty, familial strife, and oppression. His character is further developed when bushranger Harry Power enters the picture and teaches him how to despise authority. As Ned matures and descends into near-madness, people start to view him as either a hero or a murderer.

programme.title: Outlaws (?)
programme.desc: Knuck is the president of a notorious motorcycle gang who was ousted by his former subordinate and now rival Paddo. When his replacement is about to give their drug business to another gang, Knuck must fight enemies both outside and within to regain control of his leadership.

Steve Zahn, Lambert Wilson, Glynn Turman, Delroy Lindo, William H. Macy.
